Offer More Previews of a New Single & Music Video (UPDATE)|website=HYPEBEAST|access-date=2020-02-23}}</ref> <!-- Please source genres -->\n| length     = 3:58\n| label      = \n* A1\n* [[Epic Records|Epic]]\n* [[Freebandz]]\n| writer     = \n* [[Future (rapper)|Nayvadius Wilburn]]\n* [[Drake (musician)|Aubrey Graham]]\n* Darius Hill\n* [[OZ (record producer)|Ozan Yildirim]]\n* Mathias Liyew\n| producer   = \n* D. Hill\n* [[OZ (record producer)|OZ]]\n* Ambezza ({{abbr|co.|co-producer}})\n| chronology = [[Future (rapper)|Future]]\n| prev_title = Last Name\n| prev_year  = 2019\n| next_title = Dead Man Walking\n| next_year  = 2020\n| misc       = {{Extra chronology\n | artist     = [[Drake (musician)|Drake]]\n | type       = single\n | prev_title = War\n | prev_year  = 2019\n | title      = Life Is Good\n | year       = 2020\n | next_title = Desires\n | next_year  = 2020\n }}{{External music video|{{YouTube|l0U7SxXHkPY|\"Life Is Good\"}}}}\n}}\n\n\"'''Life Is Good'''\" is a song by American rapper [[Future (rapper)|Future]] featuring Canadian rapper [[Drake (musician)|Drake]]. It was released on January 10, 2020. Future and Drake notably recorded a joint mixtape, ''[[What a Time to Be Alive]]'' (2015). It was expected to be the lead single of the sequel to their mixtape,<ref name=MTV>{{cite web|url= https://www.mtv.com/news/3152082/drake-future-life-is-good-video/|title=Drake and Future Keep Losing Jobs Because They Can't Stop Dancing in 'Life Is Good'|work=[[MTV]]|last=Alston|first=Trey|date=January 10, 2020|accessdate=January 11, 2020}}</ref> however, Future confirmed it as the title track off his upcoming eight studio album.<ref name=\"Album\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.xxlmag.com/news/2020/04/future-interview-life-is-good-album/|title=Future Interview: Read His Exclusive XXL Magazine Cover Interview|work=[[XXL (magazine)|XXL]]|last=''XXL'' Staff|date=April 7, 2020|accessdate=April 7, 2020}}</ref> It debuted at number two on the US [[Billboard Hot 100|''Billboard'' Hot 100]] and became the first song ever to spend its first eight weeks at that position.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/business/chart-beat/9330849/lady-gaga-stupid-love-hot-100-debut|title=Lady Gaga's 'Stupid Love' Launches at No. 5 on Hot 100, Roddy Ricch's 'The Box' Notches Ninth Week at No. 1|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|last=Trust|first=Gary|date=March 9, 2020|accessdate=March 9, 2020}}</ref> It is Future's highest-charting song.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/business/chart-beat/8548471/roddy-ricch-the-box-hot-100-number-one-drake-future-number-two|title=Roddy Ricch's 'The Box' Rules Billboard Hot 100 for 2nd Week, Future & Drake's 'Life Is Good' Debuts at No. 2|work=Billboard|last=Trust|first=Gary|date=January 21, 2020|accessdate=January 22, 2020}}</ref> The song spent eight weeks behind [[Roddy Ricch]]'s \"[[The Box (Roddy Ricch song)|The Box]]\".\n\n== Background and music video ==\nIn late December 2019, Future and Drake were spotted in [[Atlanta]], [[Georgia (U.S. state)|Georgia]], filming a music video in a [[McDonald's]] location,<ref name=Complex>{{cite web|url= https://www.complex.com/music/2019/12/drake-future-spotted-in-mcdonalds-for-what-appears-to-be-music-video|title= Drake and Future Spotted in McDonald's Reportedly Shooting a Video |work=[[Complex (magazine)|Complex]]|last=Espinoza|first=Joshua|date=December 21, 2019|accessdate=January 11, 2020}}</ref> leading to the belief that the two had a forthcoming collaboration. The shoot included recording artists such as [[21 Savage]], [[Mike Will Made-It]], [[Lil Yachty]], [[Janelle Mon\u00e1e]] and Big Bank. Word of the video spread when media personality DJ Akademiks posted the casting call for the video. Future had previously posted a snippet of what the duo were working on in his [[Instagram]] story.<ref name=Complex/>\n\nThe song and music video, directed by [[Director X|Julien Christian Lutz]]<!--This is what he credited himself as, crossing out previous professional credits--> were released at midnight on January 10. The music video depicts Future and Drake as men with ordinary jobs, including fast food workers, mechanics, IT workers, off-brand [[Apple Store]] employees, garbagemen, chefs, aspiring rappers, and assistant directors.<ref>{{cite web|url= https://www.cnn.com/2020/01/10/entertainment/drake-future-life-good-trnd/index.html|title= Drake and Future debut 'Life is Good' video|work=[[CNN]]|last=Respers|first=Lisa|date=January 10, 2020|accessdate=January 11, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url= https://www.vulture.com/2020/01/watch-future-and-drake-hold-down-jobs-in-life-is-good-video.html|title= Future and Drake Are Just Normal, Working Joes in 'Life is Good' Video|work=[[Vulture (blog)|Vulture]]|last=Squires|first=Bethy|date=January 10, 2020|accessdate=January 11, 2020}}</ref><ref name=MTV/>\n\n== Remix ==\nOn February 15, 2020, a remix of the song was released by Future featuring Drake and American rappers [[DaBaby]] and [[Lil Baby]].<ref>{{cite news |last1=Diep |first1=Eric |title=Listen to Future and Drake's \"Life Is Good\" Remix f/ DaBaby and Lil Baby |url=https://www.complex.com/music/2020/02/future-drake-new-song-life-is-good-remix-feat-dababy-lil-baby |accessdate=February 15, 2020 |work=Complex |publisher=Complex Media, Inc. |date=February 15, 2020 |language=en}}</ref> Three days prior to the release, Future teased DaBaby and Lil Baby's vocals on an [[Instagram]] story.\n\n== Reception ==\nJason Lipshutz of ''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'' wrote that structuring the song in two halves\u2014Drake performing the first half and Future performing the latter, each with a different beat\u2014was reminiscent of Drake's previous feature on [[Travis Scott]]'s 2018 hit \"[[Sicko Mode]]\". The review praised how the artists' styles complemented each other as they did on their joint mixtape in 2015.<ref>{{cite web|url= https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop/8547741/first-stream-nselena-gomez-future-drake-mac-miller-megan-thee-stallion|title= First Stream: New Music From Selena Gomez, Future & Drake, Mac Miller & More|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|last=Lipshutz|first=Jason|date=January 10, 2020|accessdate=January 11, 2020}}</ref> ''[[XXL (magazine)|XXL]]'' described the production and instrumentation as \"dreamy\".<ref>{{cite web|url= https://www.xxlmag.com/rap-music/new-music/2020/01/drake-future-life-is-good-song/|title= Drake and Future Drop New Song \"Life Is Good\": Listen|work=[[XXL (magazine)|XXL]]|last=Coleman II|first=C. Vernon|date=January 10, 2020|accessdate=January 11, 2020}}</ref>\n\n== Personnel ==\nCredits adapted from [[Tidal (service)|Tidal]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://listen.tidal.com/album/127429589/credits|title=Life Is Good / Future|work=[[Tidal (service)|Tidal]]|accessdate=January 11, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://listen.tidal.com/album/131435179|title=Life Is Good (Remix) / Future|work=Tidal|accessdate=February 15, 2020}}</ref>\n\n* [[Future (rapper)|Future]] \u2013 principal vocalist, songwriting\n* [[Drake (musician)|Drake]] \u2013 featured vocalist, songwriting\n* D. Hill \u2013 production, songwriting\n* [[OZ (record producer)|OZ]] \u2013 production, songwriting\n* Ambezza \u2013 co-production, songwriting\n* Colin Leonard \u2013 mastering engineer\n* [[DaBaby]] \u2013 featured vocalist, songwriting {{small|(remix)}}\n* [[Lil Baby]] \u2013 featured vocalist, songwriting {{small|(remix)}}\n* Maudell Watkins \u2013 songwriting {{small|(remix)}}\n\n==Charts==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\"| Chart (2020)\n! scope=\"col\"| Peak<br />position\n|-\n{{single chart|Australia|11|artist=Future feat. Drake|song=Life Is Good|rowheader=true|accessdate=January 25, 2020}}\n|-\n{{single chart|Austria|8|artist=Future feat. Drake|song=Life Is Good|rowheader=true|accessdate=January 23, 2020}}\n|-\n{{single chart|Flanders|45|artist=Future feat. Drake|song