{"title_page": "Nahid (film)", "text_new": "{{short description|2015 film}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = Nahid\n| image          = Imgonline-com-ua-resize-JEFhdg68j4fkiwh3.jpg\n| caption        = Film poster\n| director       = [[Ida Panahandeh]]\n| producer       = Bijan Emkaniqn\n| writer         = Ida Panahandeh <br /> Arsalan Amiri\n| starring       = [[Sareh Bayat]]<br />[[Pejman Bazeghi]]<br />[[Navid Mohammadzadeh]]<br />Farideh Daryamaj\n| music          = Majid Pousti\n| cinematography = \n| editing        = Arsalan Amiri\n| distributor    = Nikan Film\n| released       = {{Film date|2015|5|16|[[2015 Cannes Film Festival|Cannes]]|df=yes}}\n| runtime        = 105 minutes\n| country        = Iran\n| language       = Persian\n}}\n'''''Nahid''''' is a 2015 Iranian [[drama film]] directed by [[Ida Panahandeh]]. It was screened in the [[Un Certain Regard]] section at the [[2015 Cannes Film Festival]] where it won a Promising Future Prize (special jury prize for debut films).<ref name=\"2015Cannes\">{{cite web |url=http://www.festival-cannes.com/en/69-editions/retrospective/2015/actualites/articles/awards-un-certain-regard-2015 |title=AWARDS - Un Certain Regard 2015 |accessdate=14 December 2017 |publisher=Festival de Cannes      }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/cannes-2015-regard-winners-announced-797333 |title=Cannes: 'Rams' Wins Un Certain Regard Prize |author=Rebecca Ford |date=23 May 2015 |accessdate=23 May 2015 |work=The Hollywood Reporter}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{IMDb title|4636046}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Nahid}}\n[[Category:2015 films]]\n[[Category:2015 drama films]]\n[[Category:Iranian films]]\n[[Category:Iranian drama films]]\n[[Category:Persian-language films]]\n[[Category:2015 directorial debut films]]\n\n\n{{Iran-film-stub}}\n{{2010s-drama-film-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{short description|2015 film}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=February 2018}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = Nahid\n| image          = Imgonline-com-ua-resize-JEFhdg68j4fkiwh3.jpg\n| caption        = Film poster\n| director       = [[Ida Panahandeh]]\n| producer       = Bijan Emkaniqn\n| writer         = Ida Panahandeh <br /> Arsalan Amiri\n| starring       = [[Sareh Bayat]]<br />[[Pejman Bazeghi]]<br />[[Navid Mohammadzadeh]]<br />Farideh Daryamaj\n| music          = Majid Pousti\n| cinematography = \n| editing        = Arsalan Amiri\n| distributor    = Nikan Film\n| released       = {{Film date|2015|5|16|[[2015 Cannes Film Festival|Cannes]]|df=yes}}\n| runtime        = 105 minutes\n| country        = Iran\n| language       = Persian\n}}\n'''''Nahid''''' is a 2015 Iranian [[drama film]] directed by [[Ida Panahandeh]]. It was screened in the [[Un Certain Regard]] section at the [[2015 Cannes Film Festival]] where it won a Promising Future Prize (special jury prize for debut films).<ref name=\"2015Cannes\">{{cite web |url=http://www.festival-cannes.com/en/69-editions/retrospective/2015/actualites/articles/awards-un-certain-regard-2015 |title=AWARDS - Un Certain Regard 2015 |accessdate=14 December 2017 |publisher=Festival de Cannes      }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/cannes-2015-regard-winners-announced-797333 |title=Cannes: 'Rams' Wins Un Certain Regard Prize |author=Rebecca Ford |date=23 May 2015 |accessdate=23 May 2015 |work=The Hollywood Reporter}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{IMDb title|4636046}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Nahid}}\n[[Category:2015 films]]\n[[Category:2015 drama films]]\n[[Category:Iranian films]]\n[[Category:Iranian drama films]]\n[[Category:Persian-language films]]\n[[Category:2015 directorial debut films]]\n\n\n{{Iran-film-stub}}\n{{2010s-drama-film-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Lugnuts", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nahid_(film)"}
{"title_page": "The Thieves (1959 film)", "text_new": "{{Infobox film\n | name =The Thieves \n | image =  The_Thieves_(1959_film) poster.jpg\n | caption = Italian poster\n | story =\n | director = [[Lucio Fulci]]\n | writer = Lucio Fulci <br> Marcello Coscia<br>Marino Onorati<br>Vittorio Vighi<br> [[Nanni Loy]]<br> [[Ottavio Jemma]]\n | starring = [[Tot\u00f2]]<br/>[[Armando Calvo]]<br/>[[Giovanna Ralli]]\n | music = [[Carlo Innocenzi]] \n | cinematography = Manuel Berenguer <br> Carlo Fiore \n | editing = Juan Pis\u00f3n<br/>Gino Talamo   \n | producer = Roberto Capitani<br/> Luigi Mondello  \n | distributor = First Line Films<br/>Bengala Film\n | released =  June 27, 1959\n | runtime = 95 minutes\n | awards =\n | country = Italy\n | language =  Italian\n | budget =\n }}\n'''''The Thieves''''' ({{lang-it|I ladri}}, {{lang-es|Contrabando en N\u00e1poles}}) is a 1959 Italian-Spanish [[comedy film|criminal comedy film]] written and directed by [[Lucio Fulci]] and starring [[Tot\u00f2]] and [[Giovanna Ralli]].<ref name=Mereghetti>{{cite book|last=Paolo Mereghetti|title=Il Mereghetti - Dizionario dei film|publisher=B.C. Dalai Editore, 2010|isbn=8860736269}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|last=Paolo Albiero, Giacomo Cacciatore|title=Il terrorista dei generi: tutto il cinema di Lucio Fulci|publisher=Un Mondo a Parte, 2004|isbn=8898395078}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|last=Alberto Anile|title=I film di Tot\u00f2 (1946-1967): la maschera tradita|publisher=Le mani, 1998|isbn=8880120808}}</ref>\n\n==Plot==\nGangster Joe Castagneto is declared undesirable by the U.S. government and returns to [[Naples]] where, under a special surveillance, he will have to deal with the hard-working and smart Police Commissioner Gennaro Di Sapio.\n\n== Cast ==\n\n*[[Tot\u00f2]] as Police Commissioner Gennaro Di Sapio\n*[[Armando Calvo]] as  Joe Castagnato/Inspector Mac Millan\n*[[Giovanna Ralli]] as  Maddalena Scognamiglio, Vincenzo's wife\n*[[Giacomo Furia]] as  Vincenzo Scognamiglio\n*[[Enzo Turco]] as  Brigadier Lanocella\n*[[Fred Buscaglione]] as Himself\n* [[Juan Jos\u00e9 Men\u00e9ndez]] as  Alberto \n* [[Rafael Luis Calvo]] as  Ciardella\n* Maria Luisa Rolando as  Concetta Improta\n* F\u00e9lix Fern\u00e1ndez as Dr. Ascione\n\n==Release==\n''The Thieves'' was released on June 27, 1959.<ref>{{cite book|last=Thrower|first=Stephen|year=1999|title=Beyond Terror: The Films of Lucio Fulci|publisher=FAB Press|ISBN=9780952926061|page=272}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n* [[List of Italian films of 1959]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{commons category|I ladri}}\n*{{IMDb title|0070843}}\n{{Lucio Fulci}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Thieves (1959 film)}}\n[[Category:Italian films]]\n[[Category:Italian crime comedy films]]\n[[Category:1950s crime comedy films]]\n[[Category:Spanish films]]\n[[Category:Spanish crime comedy films]]\n[[Category:Films directed by Lucio Fulci]]\n[[Category:Films set in Naples]]\n\n\n{{1950s-Italy-film-stub}}\n{{comedy-crime-film-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox film\n | name =The Thieves \n | image =  The_Thieves_(1959_film) poster.jpg\n | caption = Italian poster\n | story =\n | director = [[Lucio Fulci]]\n | writer = Lucio Fulci <br> Marcello Coscia<br>Marino Onorati<br>Vittorio Vighi<br> [[Nanni Loy]]<br> [[Ottavio Jemma]]\n | starring = [[Tot\u00f2]]<br/>[[Armando Calvo]]<br/>[[Giovanna Ralli]]\n | music = [[Carlo Innocenzi]] \n | cinematography = Manuel Berenguer <br> Carlo Fiore \n | editing = Juan Pis\u00f3n<br/>Gino Talamo   \n | producer = Roberto Capitani<br/> Luigi Mondello  \n | distributor = First Line Films<br/>Bengala Film\n | released =  June 27, 1959\n | runtime = 95 minutes\n | awards =\n | country = Italy\n | language =  Italian\n | budget =\n }}\n'''''The Thieves''''' ({{lang-it|I ladri}}, {{lang-es|Contrabando en N\u00e1poles}}) is a 1959 Italian-Spanish [[comedy film|criminal comedy film]] written and directed by [[Lucio Fulci]] and starring [[Tot\u00f2]] and [[Giovanna Ralli]].<ref name=Mereghetti>{{cite book|last=Paolo Mereghetti|title=Il Mereghetti - Dizionario dei film|publisher=B.C. Dalai Editore, 2010|isbn=8860736269}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|last=Paolo Albiero, Giacomo Cacciatore|title=Il terrorista dei generi: tutto il cinema di Lucio Fulci|publisher=Un Mondo a Parte, 2004|isbn=8898395078}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|last=Alberto Anile|title=I film di Tot\u00f2 (1946-1967): la maschera tradita|publisher=Le mani, 1998|isbn=8880120808}}</ref>\n\n==Plot==\nGangster Joe Castagneto is declared undesirable by the U.S. government and returns to [[Naples]] where, under a special surveillance, he will have to deal with the hard-working and smart Police Commissioner Gennaro Di Sapio.\n\n== Cast ==\n\n*[[Tot\u00f2]] as Police Commissioner Gennaro Di Sapio\n*[[Armando Calvo]] as  Joe Castagnato/Inspector Mac Millan\n*[[Giovanna Ralli]] as  Maddalena Scognamiglio, Vincenzo's wife\n*[[Giacomo Furia]] as  Vincenzo Scognamiglio\n*[[Enzo Turco]] as  Brigadier Lanocella\n*[[Fred Buscaglione]] as Himself\n* [[Juan Jos\u00e9 Men\u00e9ndez]] as  Alberto \n* [[Rafael Luis Calvo]] as  Ciardella\n* Maria Luisa Rolando as  Concetta Improta\n* F\u00e9lix Fern\u00e1ndez as Dr. Ascione\n\n==Release==\n''The Thieves'' was released on June 27, 1959.<ref>{cite book|last=Thrower|first=Stephen|year=1999|title=Beyond Terror: The Films of Lucio Fulci|publisher=FAB Press|ISBN=9780952926061|page=272}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n* [[List of Italian films of 1959]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{commons category|I ladri}}\n*{{IMDb title|0070843}}\n{{Lucio Fulci}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Thieves (1959 film)}}\n[[Category:Italian films]]\n[[Category:Italian crime comedy films]]\n[[Category:1950s crime comedy films]]\n[[Category:Spanish films]]\n[[Category:Spanish crime comedy films]]\n[[Category:Films directed by Lucio Fulci]]\n[[Category:Films set in Naples]]\n\n\n{{1950s-Italy-film-stub}}\n{{comedy-crime-film-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Grimes2", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eRelease:format cite template", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Thieves_(1959_film)"}
